Selamat ulang tahun yang ke-26, teh Sarah!

Nulis bahasa Indonesia yah sekali-sekali, maaf agak awkward. 
Gak kerasa ya, udah hampir satu tahun kita gak ketemu. Rasanya baru kemarin curhat dramatis percintaan sambil makan waffle, baru kemarin nginep di perpustakaan baca jurnal dan belajar buat ujian, baru kemarin makan tantuni bareng tengah malam, gak peduli asrama punya giriş saati mumpung udah tingkat akhir, baru kemarin nonton horror sambil buli @arhas27 supaya ngadep layar, baru kemarin keluyuran ke espark belanja padahal uang terbatas, baru kemarin sarapan weekend bareng di pinggir porsuk, baru kemarin fangirling dan gibah k-pop bareng.. Bahkan rasanya baru kemarin jemput Teh Sar untuk pertama kalinya dari otogar XD

Tiga tahun yang lumayan seru yah, teh. Semoga sama berkesannya untuk tehsar. Kita emang bakal lumayan susah ketemu sekarang dan mungkin selanjutnya, tapi yang jelas seninle geçirdiğim yılları asla unutmayacağım. Tehsar sudah berperan besar dalam tiga tahun terpentingku di Turki, semoga persahabatan kita bisa terus berlanjut yah.

Semoga tehsar semakin sukses dalam karir, percintaan, dan hidup in general. Bangga deh tehsar jadi peneliti kanker sekarang wqwqwq. Iyi ki doğdun, tehsar, seni seviyorum ❤

caption.text:
Yesterday my high school best friend finally tied the knot. It's not like this is the first time someone from my friend circle got married but this one felt especially different 😂 
This girl was my partner in almost everything during high school: music club, student council, we both live in Cimahi so we're the constant teasing targets of our school friends (Bandung coret lmao), my seblak, bolang, concert, kupi, curhat, momotoran, Cimahi Metal, getting home late partner. I think I was even her manager for her photo modeling gigs sometimes 😂 .I know all of her past relationships (though not very updated on the details since college started as we're always thousands miles apart). And now.... She's (not-so) suddenly married.

Mam, you deserve happiness because you're one of the toughest yet most gentle women I know. You are determined, you don't give up even if you need to sacrifice a lot. You are smart and you are beautiful. Now you are a grown up, a doctor with a husband and a lot of responsibilities that you're ready to fulfill. I can say that I can't be more proud. I can't believe that it's been seven years since we were seventeen 😂 
Have a great life together, Rahma and Amri! And although Rahma is very far from what I'd call fragile, please take care of your (hits terbaik bandung, high school gadis ponds and gadis hai) wife, Amri. You are both lucky to have found each other 😊 
PS: The lady in red is my mom. Ironically, my parents attended the wedding and I didn't 😭 And girls, you look amazing!! #wedding #bestfriends #highschool

caption.text:
Türkiye'den mezun olalı sanki sadece bir hafta olmuş gibi hissediyorum.

Kampüse gidip gelmek, Espark ve Çarşı'da alışveriş yapmak, kütüphanede bazı sınavlar için bütün gece ders çalışmak, A1*01'den abur cubur alıp dersi beklerken kampüsun içindeki parkta piknik yapmak, en aptal konular üzerinde tartışmak, birbirimizle dalga geçmek, bazen beraber yemek pişirmek (sen yemek pişirirken ben seni rahatsız etmek için youtube'da çalan şarkiları çok sesli bir şekilde söylüyorum), derslerden sonra senin evine gidip uşenmek, beraber çay içerek sohbet etmek. Hepsini çok özledim, özellikle seninle beraber vakit geçirmeyi çok özledim. 
Bir yıl oldu biz ayrılalı, ama bugüne kadar senin gibi bir arkadaşı bulamadım. Senin gibi beni çok iyi anlayan, senin kadar güzel, çalışkan, sabırlı, eğlenceli, ve iyi kalpli biri bulmak ne kadar zor olduğunu umarım biliyorsun.

Ah Aylarochka, Türkiye'deyken dört büçük yıl çok kısa bir zaman düşüneceğimi hiç beklemiyordum. Dört büçük yıl uzundur, maalesef senin gibi biriyle geçırmek için, bence on yıl bile yetmez.

Hayat devam ediyor işte, herkes bunu söylüyor. Easier said than done, indeed. (Sanki sevgilime yazıyormuşum gibi, ama nasıl corny olabildiğimi iyi biliyorsun 😂) 25. Doğum günün kutlu olsun, Aylarochka. Allah'a tek bir dileğim var, nerede olursan ve ne yaparsan da umarım her zaman mutlu olursun çünkü sen mutluluğu hak ediyorsun 😊 
Tekrar görüşürüz~

caption.text:
Although history may beg to differ, 22 December is known as Mother's Day to most Indonesians. So I guess there's no harm in simply expressing my most sincere gratitude to all mothers everywhere, and especially to my own mom.

My mother in my eyes is a person so hardworking and dedicated. She's so dedicated in raising her children, taking care of her husband, and educating her students. She thinks of, cares for and sympathizes with too many people, I lost count. Unlike me, she's one of those people who often contact people only to ask how they are and is always ready to offer help if needed.

She might have her own career and ambitions but until now, I think she's one of the most selfless people that I know personally of. For her, the greatest success is the success of people around her, no matter if it's her husband, her children, her students, her relatives, her friends, or even other people that she might not know 😀

She never fails to make me reflect on my life and my mindset. When some meaningless ambitions begin to cloud my judgment, thinking about what she would do were she in my position usually helps tone them down.

I just love her a tad bit too much, I guess.

Happy Mother's Day, mom. Hope you're having a great day 😀 ((Note: 22 December actually marks the day where women from all over Indonesia met 88 years ago in a congress to fight for the improvement of their rights in various aspects, including politics. This day should be treated as important as Mother's Day)) #mothersday #mother #mom

caption.text:
Finally turned 24 today and I honestly don't know what to feel about this.
The past one year was an important time for me personally. I finally got just a glimpse of real life. A heartbreak, consecutive separations with people and a place that I loved, moving on and settling into a new environment. A failure, a success, a status quo. Encountering problems, both small and big ones. Bad news and good news casually take turns coming and going and new worries about everything start to pile up inside me.

On some days I would think about all what ifs and on the other days I would simply shrug everything off and just live in the moment. 
But in the end, I'm just thankful to God I can still live to this moment and get to experience all these things. Who knows when these lessons will come in handy?

I sincerely thank everyone for the birthday greetings and wishes. They are all lovely and have certainly made my day. But mostly, I want to thank everyone who have made my year beautiful. Sorry if this comes off a bit corny, I'm not good with words.

Just thank you 😊

So far the biggest pit discovered, Excavation Pit No.1 at Terracotta Army Museum, Xi'an.

Some short background story for nerds like me:

Qin Shihuang was an infamous tyrant that buried alive hundreds of scholars, loved to show his power by using severe punishments, even to his own family members, made many people live in constant fear and many other terrible things that showed if humaneness probably was absent from his life. But he also made tremendous achievements such as unifying China and ending hundreds of years of warfare, instituting a system of meritocracy where merits and accomplishments were more important than ancestry, initiating the building of The Great Wall of China to protect his state from nomads, establishing a standardized writing and measurement system.

He was afraid of death, terrified that in the after life, people whom he had done wrong would seek a revenge so he ordered thousands of workers to make a gigantic mausoleum with sets of thousands of life-size pottery soldiers to frighten the revengeful souls. The positions of these soldiers resemble their positions during a war. Other than pottery soldiers, real bronze weaponry, and rivers of mercury that he believed was 'elixir of life' are also present. His tomb itself is still yet to be excavated as the Chinese government doesn't want to risk spoiling it before the right technology is used.

It was said that many soldiers, concubines, and even engineers and architects that helped build the mausoleum were also sealed alive inside after Qin Shihuang's death.

I sincerely hope that his tomb will be excavated in my life time. I would want to go and see! 😢

caption.text:
Big Wild Goose Pagoda, Xi'an.

One of the most well-preserved of its kind. Built during Tang Dynasty in 7th century, it was used to collect Buddhist materials from India translated into Chinese from Sanskrit.

#bigwildgoosepagoda #pagoda #buddhism #silkroad #tangdynasty #xian #china #trip #winterholiday

South Gate of Xi'an City Wall.

This wall was first built during the old Tang dynasty between 7th to 10th century. It has been enlarged several times and now it covers almost 14 kilometers in length.

We toured the whole wall today by bike (an accomplishment for weakling me esp after Huashan yesterday lol). Unfortunately Xi'an was foggy (and polluted) today and we couldn't see a lot of things very clearly. Still beautiful nonetheless.

PS: This was taken when the sky was already dark lol don't worry, the pollution was bad but it's still not that bad 😂

#xian #china #citywall #fortification #winterholiday #nofilter #triptoXian

Other than its breathtaking sceneries, Huashan is also famous for its Taoist monasteries. Long time ago monks used to climb the rocky mountain and its multiple peaks to seek peace. However, due to the pretty hard access, the temples were never very popular among pilgrims.

I somehow found the temples (no matter how colorful they can be sometimes) to be perfectly in harmony with the nature. Simply gorgeous.

#huashan #huayin #china #华山 #中国 #winterholiday

caption.text:
Another city corner that I managed to visit alone.

I've always been interested in studying anything grim in human history, I read, I watch, I dig as much information as I can. It tortures me and I often end up not being able to sleep at night yet I can't help but keep doing it. Sometimes I just want to make sure if I still have a working conscience.

This city was a place where a terrific human tragedy occured once.

Hundreds of thousands of people were once mass slaughtered only in the span of six weeks, women raped, children shot to death, businesses looted, putrid smell from the burnt corpses of civilian in every corner of the city.

Let those who suffered and died finally find their peace. Let those who committed such atrocity pay for what they did. And let us work together not to let these things happen ever again.

This might be only one side of the story, things might be exaggerated for all I know. But massacre did happen, no matter how many were tortured and executed. This should be a lesson for all of us to reflect over.

PS: The museum is excellent. Very modern, rich of information, and well-maintained. All texts are in three languages: Mandarin, English, Japanese. The museum (+the mass grave and the sculptures) succeeds to portray the horror of the tragedy very well. Totally recommended. Especially for those who are interested in dark tourism (like me). #nanjing #nanjingmassacre

caption.text:
To be honest, during my first years in Turkey I'd never really been close to my fellow Indonesian friends. Just occasionally coming to some of their gatherings to enjoy Indonesian foods and chat about our mundane lives in our mother tongue. I don't remember exactly how and why but our relationships began to get so much better (not that it wasn't good before) starting in 2014.

Although we didn't get to meet everyday or share every single detail about our lives, I'm glad they were there. They were whom I looked for when I missed home, and though not the only ones, they were also among those who always supported me during my highs and lows. I repeatedly say that I meet all kinds of great people in Turkey and that statement is never exclusive to my foreign friends. It applies to these wonderful and smart Indonesians from all around the country as well. 
They will always have a special place in my heart as my very good friends and my Indonesian family in Turkey. I hope we'll keep in touch 😃

As for Tea abla, we haven't known each other for very long but we sure have grown close to each other. I'll miss her straightforwardness, her advices, her company. She is always welcome in Indonesia (and don't forget, breakfast included 😉). See you when I see you again, guys 😊☺️ #farewelledition #indonesians #friends #eskişehir #georgian #turkey #vscocam

I hope that today was simply a 'see you later' and not an absolute 'good bye'. I couldn't help but cry a bit. It feels like I finally ended things with my long term boyfriend lmao. I have known her for almost five years and spent almost everyday (minus summers and an exchange term) for the last four years together. 
I'll tell you one thing: Time does fly and studying abroad makes everything even harder. We get attached to people or customs we are bound to leave one day. 
We talked about a lot of stuffs that are now left undone, planned a lot of trips that unfortunately couldn't come true due to limited time we had.

Today's farewell is bittersweet to me. Life goes on and we will also move on from whatever comfort zone we are in. Aylar and I are currently undergoing this process. The only thing that somehow gives me assurance and a sense of comfort is the fact that we're going to have another exciting adventure and eventually do things that we love, only in different places.

I wish the best for her and her future endeavors. She deserves a lot of good things in life 👼🙆 #friends #besties #turkey #turkmen #vscocam

caption.text:
Freiheitstrasse or 'Freedom Street' is a street in Hamburg's sex district, Reeperbahn.

Contrary to what many would assume, the name of the street has nothing to do with 'sex and nightlife freedom' or anything. It, instead, is related to the past, when Reeperbahn was still an area where rope makers made ends meet some three or four centuries ago. Freiheitstrasse was one of the first places that were granted religious freedom in Hamburg. 
The first pubs where The Beatles played after getting constantly denied of gigs in Liverpool also belong in this street. 
Fun fact #1: John Lennon was infamous for his rebellious nature during his time in Hamburg. There was a rumor that he robbed somebody once at Freiheitstrasse. Until today many Hamburgers still make a joke out of it, "If somebody robs you, ask for his autograph. He might be the next John Lennon". Fun fact #2: The pub where The Beatles played their very first gig in Hamburg is called 'Indra' (this fact is only fun to me bcs my dad's name is Indra lol there's nothing uncommon with the fact).
#hamburg #germany #travel #trip #freiheitstrasse #vscocam

Rathaus (Town hall) of Hamburg. This building was completed in 1897, 55 years after The Great Fire destroyed the bigger part of the city, including three main churches and the old city hall.

Hamburg has always been one of the most wealthy areas in Germany and Europe. The beautiful Rathaus built from expensive and huge stones had been intended to show exactly their prestigious status back then. 
#rathaus #cityhall #hamburg #germany #travel #vscocam

20 facts about me
1. One can never spell nor pronounce my name right at the first try. My bus tickets, old student card, a certificate are proofs of that.
2. My academic life (almost) has always been planned by my mom. I'm simply doing the hardwork to fulfill her targets. But I have no reason to go against her since everything makes sense even to myself.
3. I can read since I was 3.
4. I started wearing glasses when I was 3, ditched it in middle school bcs 'it doesn't look pretty'. I was a teenager. Don't judge.
4. I prefer books with facts and evidences (esp historical) than ones of fantasies.
5. I have a younger brother who makes many friends of mine willingly call me 'sister-in-law'.
6. I don't like working for partisan organizations.
7. I constantly get second-hand embarrassment bcs of my bestfriends. And they do to bcs of me. Mutual relationship.
8. I and my closest friend in Turkey @aylarmoons have telepathy. We buy SAME things (bags, clothes, perfume) all the time without planning it. We hate this.
9. I am not a nationalist nor an overly religious person. I'm simply a normal human being who cares about the well-being of other humans.
10. My truest identity is a fangirl.
